annotation.TEXT: Argh! How'd I screw that up? Now's not the time for stupid mistakes!
Okay, here we've got autoscrolling and a layer 2 that scrolls at a different rate. That's pretty clever. Also, I think this room will be mostly easier than the previous two rooms.

Well, here we go. ♥-4, the final trial! I've gone over raocow's video of this level to help prepare me for this, but I am not going to begin with the reserve invincibility star like he did! (But if I die five times, I will use it.)
Well, somebody did vote for a king combo a couple episodes ago...
Update: marcelodiedara got it. It's Killer Instinct (SNES).
CALCULATIONS COMPLETE. THE ANSWER IS... OMGWTHIT?!
"Fox, get this guy off me!" (No, it's not that Slippy.)
Yikes! That was close! Come on, I've already finished the hardest stuff in this level, and I wouldn't want to die now! (I wouldn't want to die at all anyway!)
I liked the name "Soft and Fluffy Mantle" for 2-5 better, but I guess that wouldn't fit here.
Also, I believe 6-B's level name "SWIM OR RUN?" was already in English to begin with. Oh, and since the warp star is now revealed, does that mean I won't get sent to a TEST level now?
Well, I had no idea that 1♥P was here all this time! Is there anything else hidden around here?
Pop quiz: What game was that? First to answer correctly gets 3 Happy Smile points!
Ah, so ♥-3 is "SKY", not "EMPTY". Okay. I was wondering which one it was.

Yep! This means I won't ever be trapped in world 6 now if I enter it from that side! That's cool! And this concludes the English level name tour! Now, let's get to this episode's voting results and see where I'm heading next...
Oh, another typo. That should be "BOB-OMB", not "BOM-OMB".

Oh, man. So, I already figured I was only going to do one new level today, because of how much time I spent showing off the English level names, but you guys just had to send me to quite possibly the hardest level in the hack now, didn't you?
Agh, once again, I'm double-hitting with my cape spins. I should just stick with hitting the blocks from below. Fortunately, I believe the cape lets me skip a midair springboard jump here!
Whoops. Well, so much for my plan on using that Goomba to swim faster...
No, seriously! It's... OMGWTHIT?! ("Oh my god what the heck is this?!") I'm not kidding! Just watch!

Well, anyway, the first room is now complete, and I think it was the hardest room in this level. Sure, other rooms like this next one are also challenging, but not nearly as "OMGWTHIT?!" as that layer 2 wind room!
BEEP BEEP BLIP BEEP... NOW CALCULATING... NOW CALCULATING...
Awesome. And now there's another ON/OFF block right there that I can use.
This yellow pipe I believe acts as a reset pipe.

Oh, this is interesting. The level dot for 6-B and the warp star here are revealed now. Also, I was told that the paths to 6-A and 6-6 might not be accessible from this side now. However, they still are, but that's probably only because this file was started before the version update, so this file's overworld paths are already determined.
Yeah, I remember that shell block from raocow's run. It's quite helpful here.
And, there you go. Those are the 11 levels that you guys can vote for. So, place your votes, and we'll find out where I head next time!
Yes, we totally need more English!
Just barely dodged that one!
Oh, while I'm in the area, I guess I should clean out 2-A's star coins now.
And now we have a kicked shell thrown into the mix. Umm... Yay? Also, for whatever reason here, I spend a while trying to see if I can despawn the shell.
Oh, and I guess there weren't any message boxes in this level. Okay, let's get out of here.
Of course, it would help if I only hit the blocks once, and not twice when I did my cape spins on them. Maybe it would be easier to just bonk the blocks from below like normal.
Careful! Don't hit this ON/OFF block, or you will fall to your death!
Ehh... Probably not. Okay, let's move on. Now, what I'm going to do here is spend some time travelling around the map and showing off the English names of every level that I have access to right now.
Whoa, wait a minute! I just found something totally by accident!
"FLOWERS LEAD" was already in English to begin with.
Once you reach the note blocks, you technically don't need Wiggler anymore.
Alright, let's memorize the terrain here...
And here's midpoint! Yes, I am halfway done with this level! But, the next room I think is the second-hardest room in this level!
I don't know if there's like a hidden message in the fragile blocks here, but the fragile blocks towards the top are made of double-sized Tetris blocks!
Oh, hey there, Depth Charge Lakitu! How's it going?
Oh, now this room is neat. Check out this gimmick.

Well, that level was quite something, and I'm so glad it went so well for me! (I was most concerned about the wind room at the start and the rope/lava/saw room just after midpoint. Once I got to the ON/OFF vision obscuring room, I figured I'd be alright.)

Now, raocow had the benefit of the invincibility star there, so he didn't have to do that "OMGWTHIT?!" maneuver! I am astonished that I pulled that off on my first try! Is that seriously how I'm supposed to get through that spot?
And now, it's disco time! If you have a cape, this is so much easier.
Parakoopa bounce to hit this ON/OFF switch.
Yes, I'm now playing that version update that fixes the missing star coin problem in 2-A, and includes an English version of the hack!

However, oddly enough, it turns blue after being used. Did it actually take me to a completely different sublevel? Or is this just a color glitch similar to the original game's Donut Secret 1 side area? (LOL)
If I'm going too fast for you to read all these, then feel free to pause the video as needed.
Wait, I think I did this part wrong, but that's okay.
Okay, just take it nice and easy, and analyze how I need to move to avoid becoming a pin cushion...
D'oh! I moved incorrectly there, and now I'm on my last hit!
Of course, be very careful of the maces.
Now, similar to world 9-4 in The Lost Levels, the blocks in this area spell out a message in Japanese.
No clue. Let's just move on.
Now, fry carefully, and try to get your fireballs to ascend through the frozen blocks, because you will need to ascend!
Oh, man. Line-guided ropes. Definitely duck-jump onto the first one. You want your hitbox as small as possible!
And, with that, world ♥ is now complete! However, I'm far from done! There's still tons of levels left to play! Let me quickly go around and point out which levels you guys can vote on like usual...
Whoa, wait. "HURTFUL Hearts"? I thought I was told that it was "HEARTFUL Hearts". Is it supposed to be "HURTFUL"?
Zmw mld, ofwrxilfh hkvvw ylmfh tznv.
Bonus game average so far: 188 / 26 = 7.231 1♥Ps each.

Ah, now we're getting trickier. The ON/OFF blocks also control whether or not certain green blocks are solid or not. These green blocks turn solid at the same time that your view of them gets obscured. Remember where they are!
Alright, and now back to our regularly scheduled showing of English level names.
Aim your jumps carefully here!
Didn't even really have to memorize much there.
Once again, my cape is helpful, this time for killing undead duders.
Yay for doing things the unorthodox way!
Wow, those depth charge spinies make this part tricky!
Also, I intend to show off the post-boss dialogues that I've already done in English next time as well! To be continued...

Whoa, almost had a fatal slip up right at the start! One hit here is probably instant death (unless I can somehow retrieve my reserve cape), since the layer 2 wind here won't support me without a cape.
OMGHDINDT?! ("Oh my god how did I not die there?!")

Nuts! Couldn't keep my reserve cape either, but that's okay, since I was going to want to switch to these flowers for this next part anyway. (Even now, I'm getting lucky with the timing of replacement power ups when I get hit!)
Okay, now I'm swimming...
Bah! My first mistake in this level. Fortunately, it's non-lethal, but... owww...
Oh, what's this? The level names... They're in English now!
Huh. Why would there be a Thwimp on the right? Well, it jumped off screen, but why was it there in the first place? Is there a hidden item over there?
Nice. Nailed that first try, though that's not as "OMGWTHIT?!"-inducing as that one part in the previous wind area! And now room 2 is done...
And right there, I fell off the screen! But, fortunately, I managed to come back! Now, how do I do this next part...
Can't kill Thwimps though, but they should be easy enough to get past.
Honestly, why did I even waste my time trying to despawn the shell? This part's not even that hard. 9-2 had far worse stuff!
Good enough. That was kind of a tight squeeze back there, but I made it.
Yeah, that was the midair bounce that I just skipped right there. Now I gotta "R"...
Okay, I can totally do this...
If this part of the video looks a bit choppy, I blame the wind. For some reason, patterns like this tend to mess with a video's frame rate.
The landmasses never actually go away, but the ON/OFF switches actually determine which pieces of land are obscured from your vision. Hope your memory is good!
Oh, and keep in mind that I now won't get trapped in world 6 at all, since the warp star is working properly from this side now!
Oh, there it is! The last star coin is right here at the end! Alright, now I have finally collected five star coins in 2-A!
Pressing "R" to allow you to see further ahead while doing this is definitely useful.
Whoa! How did I not get third-degree burns there?!

Now we have to do some Wiggler bouncing. First of all, duck-jump onto the Wiggler. This way, you have more leeway with the overhead munchers. Also, try to balance on the right half of Wiggler's head to keep it from suddenly changing directions on you.
BGM: Castlevania: Aria of Sorrow - Castle Corridor
Alright, in this room, bounce off of parakoopduders and fragile blocks, and just keep ascending! It's not very hard, but you definitely don't want to screw this up!
Some of that wasn't quite as tricky as it looked, but it was certainly still tricky!
Alright, that's it... Except it isn't, since I can still access a few world 6 levels...
Now, let's see... What should I show off first? Umm... Was there a message box in the starting house?
Oh, hey there Chuck. I have no idea whether you're a bouncer or a splitter, but I don't care.
FINISH!!!
Well, this sign over here (that I think says "Ma & Lu") is still in Japanese.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Now, before I get to the voting results... Guess what?
And now Lakitu's gone away, and I claim the final star coin, and proceed to the very last room!
Saw the opportunity for the 1♥P combo there, and decided to go for it!
Whoops! I think that's a typo. Shouldn't that be "WIGGLER'S" instead of "WRIGGLER'S"?
Whoa, he killed my Wiggler! But, at least I stomped his shell!
According to the comments in raocow's video of this level, this translates to "Thank you☆". And, to that I say, "You're welcome♥"!
Whoa! Yeah, I just felt like doing that for no real reason.
Whoa, another close call. I almost hit the underside of those spikes back there.
BGM: Donkey Kong (GB) - Showdown at the Tower
Okay, using what I know, I should line myself up with the vertical guy when I jump.
There's this hack's infamous cutoff lava! Also, this place is filled with saws too.
Okay, so we've got that single block there lined up with the vertical paradooder, and the cement L-shape coming out of the ceiling...
Goal tape average so far: 2614 / 67 = 39.015 stars each.
